  <h1 class="page-title">about</h1>

  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm Cyrus (<span lang="fa" dir="rtl">کوروش</span>, the name is
      Persian), a staff software engineer at Meta in New York, working
      on ads ranking AI.
    </p>
    <p>
      I've spent a bit over a decade building ML systems: recommenders
      at Dollar Shave Club, LLM fine tuning at Google, the ML platform
      at HBO Max, and now ranking models that serve billions of people,
      plus agent workflows that run their own experiments.
    </p>
    <p>
      For two of those years I was an engineering manager, leading a 15
      engineer ads ranking team at Meta. In May 2026 I went back to
      being an IC. I like building too much to stay out of the code.
    </p>

    <h2>the path here</h2>
    <pre><code>2026 – now   Meta          staff swe, ads ranking ai
2024 – 2026  Meta          engineering manager, ml
2022 – 2024  HBO Max       engineering manager, ml platform
2020 – 2022  Google        senior swe, ml
2019 – 2020  Dollar Shave  lead ml engineer
2017 – 2018  Facebook      data scientist
2015 – 2017  Hulu          data scientist
2013 – 2015  Microsoft     data scientist, azure
             U. Maryland   bs, mathematics &amp; biology</code></pre>

    <h2>off the clock</h2>
    <p>
      I build things that don't need a roadmap review: a computer
      vision pipeline that <a href="/work/nba-video-analysis">watches
      NBA games from broadcast video</a>, a
      <a href="/work/poe-league-tools">leveling copilot for Path of
      Exile</a>, and a rotating cast of LLM experiments.
    </p>
    <p>
      The common thread: systems that are honest about what they know.
      Models that abstain instead of guessing.
    </p>

